content.description: Some technical vertical climbing past a perma-draw leads to overhung jugs.
content.protection: 7 bolts plus one perma-draw to an anchor with mussies.
content.location: The left-most bolted line in this sector. Has a perma-draw at mid height.

content.description: Much like Wingman with technical vertical climbing in the 1st half leading to overhanging jugs in the second half. Trend left after the last bolt to the Wingman anchors.
content.protection: 8 bolts sharing the mussied anchor on Wingman to the left.
content.location: The next route right of Wingman sharing its anchors.

content.description: A tough start for the grade leads to jugs and a bit of a runout up and left to the anchors.
content.protection: 7 bolts to an anchor with fixed lower off biners.
content.location: Just right of Stage 5 Clinger around the nose of rock separating the steep left panel in this sector from the more moderately angled right hand panel.

content.description: Another tough start for the grade on questionable rock leads to easier climbing above.
content.protection: 8 bolts to an anchor with fixed lower off biners.
content.location: The middle route on the lower angled right hand side panel of this sector.

content.description: Another technical start up through questionable rock to an easier juggy finish.
content.protection: 7 bolts to anchor with fixed lower off biners.
content.location: The right-most bolted line in this sector.

content.description: Technical moves down low lead to jugs up high as is standard for this panel. The last clip before the anchors is a perma-draw.
content.protection: 5 bolts plus one perma-draw. Anchors with fixed lower off biners.
content.location: The third route from the left side of this sector and the right-most route on the overhung panel forming the left side of this sector.
